{
  "texts": [
    "PCA: (Paid Commercial Actor) Variable referring to the usage of GenAI by a paid commercial actor or Example 1: (FA) \"AI bot campaign utilized by the Russians\" \"AIpowered influence campaign by Israeli corporation with state affiliation\" Example 2: (PPC) \"Deepfake of former political leader endorsing current candidate\" \"AI speech material generated by opposition candidate for election\" Example 3: (PCA) \"Consultancy group hired to establish an AI bot network to call potential voters in rural regions\" corporate entity, relevant to an election.",
    "PG: (Partisan Group) Variable referring to the use of GenAI by a group not officially affiliated with a political party but with clear political beliefs, relevant to an election.",
    "GOVERNMENT: Variable referring to the use of GenAI by a government authority in power, relevant to an election.",
    "UC: (Unclear) Variable referring to the use of GenAI by an unspecified actor, relevant to an election.",
    "Example 4: (PG) \"Pro-BJP social media group created pro-Modi deepfakes on Instagram\" Example 5: (Government) \"Government-established AI tools to verify voter candidacy in an election period\" Example 6: (UC) \"AI-generated deepfakes of leading political candidates with no clear origin\" Good or Bad Usage G: (Good) Variable referring to the use of GenAI for an ostensibly good purpose, relevant to an election."
